Colombian Stocks: Almacenes Exito, Canacol, Fabricato

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-01T20:10:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/colombian-stocks-almacenes-exito-falls-canacol-fabricato-rise.html
(Corrects percent discount in third paragraph.)  The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:06 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.8 percent to 13,524.25, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.6 percent to 1,652.34.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s biggest retailer,
fell 2 percent to 23,000 pesos. The company said yesterday it
will offer shares in the local market at an 8.1 percent discount
from the Aug. 30 closing price.  The Medellin-based company will offer to sell 114.27
million shares at 21,900 pesos each, it said in a regulatory
filing yesterday.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Toronto-based  oil
company  with fields in Colombia, rose 2.2 percent to 1,645
pesos. Canacol said it was awarded a contract from Ecopetrol SA,
Colombia’s biggest oil company, to buy gas and gas liquids from
the Rancho Hermoso field in the Llanos basin, according to a
regulatory filing today.  Fabricato SA (FABRI CB),  Colombia ’s biggest textile maker,
rose 0.7 percent to 73.5 pesos. The company said it has paid off
all but 3.3 billion pesos ($1.9 million), or 1 percent of its
total debt when it began restructuring under the country’s
bankruptcy law in 2000, according to a regulatory filing
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
